                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>Letters are wide and well-defined. Pronounced serifs on all letters. Cross-bar on 'As' in lines 3-4 are short. Hederae used in lines 1 and 4. The hedera in line 1 is large (the size of the other characters) and in outline only. The hederae in line 4 are small. Most letters are straight, except line three where they slope to the right.</p>
